25/09/2003
GUNJA, Croatia -- Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) and Croatia officially opened a new border crossing at the Sava River on Wednesday (24 September). The new facility links the towns of Brcko in BiH and Gunja in Croatia through the Fortuna Bridge and is part of a larger project to improve transport and trade activities in Southeast Europe.
Meanwhile in Bulgaria on Wednesday, the regional ministry opened a tender for supply of equipment to three border crossings with Greece. The EU will finance the project. (Dnevnik - 25/09/03; HINA - 24/09/03)
